(40, 14, 35, 41, 3, 8, 10, 'brought unto him all that were diseased', 'Healing and Multitudes', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of large crowds seeking healing from Jesus. In Matthew, the men brought all the diseased, while in Mark, the multitude pressed upon him to touch him due to his healing miracles.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
